<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0598 </DOCNO><TEXT>The spondylometaphyseal dysplasias are a very heterogeneous group of disorders.Only one has been clearly defined, namely, the spondylometaphyseal dysplasia- Kozlowski type, known also as the 'common type'. This disorder is inheritedas an autosomal dominant trait. In this report we describe an Arabic-Moslemkindred with spondylometaphyseal dysplasia, not of the common type, withan autosomal dominant mode of inheritance, indicating further heterogeneity.</TEXT></DOC>